# Garelier nested .ignore (ripgrep / fd) — lives at __garelier/.ignore
#
# DEC-051: Garelier never edits the project's ROOT .ignore. ripgrep and fd honor
# nested .ignore files, so these patterns are RELATIVE TO __garelier/ and apply
# to every <pm_id> under it. Project build dirs (e.g. target/) are the project's
# own concern — Garelier only ignores its own runtime / worktree trees.
*/runtime/
*/_workers/
*/_scouts/
*/_smiths/
*/_librarians/
*/_observers/
*/_artisan/
*/_guardians/
*/_dock/
